I've got a lot of people
rooting for me back home:

22:53.163 --> 22:56.333
<i>all the guys on the SWAT team,</i>
<i>my family, my friends,</i>

22:56.333 --> 22:58.711
<i>even people I've arrested.</i>

22:58.711 --> 23:02.214
I end up with
a captive audience, right?

23:02.214 --> 23:04.425
- Bladesmiths, you only have

23:04.425 --> 23:06.844
30 minutes remaining
to finish your work.

23:06.844 --> 23:08.929
<i>- On one side of my blade</i>

23:08.929 --> 23:12.224
there are definitely a few
cold shuts that are apparent,

23:12.224 --> 23:16.103
that might end up
under extreme abuse,

23:16.103 --> 23:19.857
but you get to a
certain point where you know

23:19.857 --> 23:22.026
there are issues
with your blade,

23:22.026 --> 23:25.321
<i>and to address them,</i>
<i>you could basically ruin it.</i>

23:25.321 --> 23:29.366
So I'm just working on
refining my blade

23:29.366 --> 23:32.703
and I'm trying to stay far,
far away from cold shuts.

23:32.703 --> 23:34.538
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:34.538 --> 23:36.290
- Bah!

23:36.290 --> 23:38.000
- Frank thinks he's gonna
take the belt.

23:38.000 --> 23:39.919
- Oh, yeah.
- Hey, that's the way to think.

23:39.919 --> 23:41.754
- How we doing, guys?

23:41.754 --> 23:43.422
I'm very competitive.
Beautiful.

23:43.422 --> 23:45.716
I don't like to lose.
Second sucks.

23:45.716 --> 23:48.719
- There you go, yeah, yeah.
- Went with carbon fiber.

23:48.719 --> 23:50.679
<i>- Me and my daughter,</i>
<i>even though she's three,</i>

23:50.679 --> 23:52.389
<i>I even get</i>
<i>competitive with her.</i>

23:52.389 --> 23:54.350
I mean, sometimes I have
to take a step back

23:54.350 --> 23:56.518
and let her win.

23:56.518 --> 23:59.104
- Five, four, three,

23:59.104 --> 24:01.482
two, one.

24:01.482 --> 24:03.108
Bladesmiths, shut down
your machines.

24:03.108 --> 24:05.611
Drop your tools.
This round is over.

24:05.611 --> 24:08.948
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:08.948 --> 24:11.742
<i>- Overall, I feel great</i>
<i>about my final blade.</i>

24:11.742 --> 24:13.160
<i>It's out of my hands</i>
<i>at this point,</i>

24:13.160 --> 24:16.205
so whatever happens
is gonna happen.

24:16.205 --> 24:19.625
- Bladesmiths,
this is the strength test.

24:19.625 --> 24:22.086
To test the strength
and durability of your blades,

24:22.086 --> 24:23.754
I'm going to be taking
each of your knives

24:23.754 --> 24:25.881
and chopping into
these buttstocks ten times.

24:25.881 --> 24:28.300
Remember, in this test,
it's not what your knife

24:28.300 --> 24:29.927
does to the buttstock
that counts.

24:29.927 --> 24:31.595
It's what the buttstock
does to your knives.

24:31.595 --> 24:33.847
Tony, you're up first.
Are you ready?

24:33.847 --> 24:35.265
- Get 'er done.

24:35.265 --> 24:37.726
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:37.726 --> 24:39.853
<i>If there's gonna</i>
<i>be a failure on my blade,</i>

24:39.853 --> 24:42.189
<i>it's gonna go</i>
<i>at the chop test,</i>

24:42.189 --> 24:45.359
but I'm not nervous
because I've done all I can.

24:45.359 --> 24:47.111
<i>There's nothing more to do.</i>

24:47.111 --> 24:54.076
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:00.332 --> 25:03.419
- Well, Tony, first thing,
there's a little bit

25:03.419 --> 25:05.295
of deflection
of the edge right here,

25:05.295 --> 25:08.382
but the rest of the blade
held up pretty well.

25:08.382 --> 25:10.259
Well done.
- Thank you.

25:10.259 --> 25:12.052
- Corey, you're up.
Are you ready?

25:12.052 --> 25:13.762
- Absolutely.
- All right.

25:13.762 --> 25:16.306
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:16.306 --> 25:18.392
<i>- I really don't know</i>
<i>anything about a gun stock.</i>

25:18.392 --> 25:21.687
<i>It's probably not some</i>
<i>kind of, like, soft pine.</i>

25:21.687 --> 25:23.856
It's probably not gonna
be easy on the blade.

25:25.733 --> 25:39.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:39.955 --> 25:42.624
- Well, Corey, I'm not supposed
to work on your knives,

25:42.624 --> 25:46.170
but I think I put another
thumb groove on this side.

25:46.170 --> 25:49.465
It's rolled
completely around.

25:49.465 --> 25:52.801
The handle is also
very narrow in this dimension,

25:52.801 --> 25:54.720
and really wide
in this dimension.

25:54.720 --> 25:57.264
It's almost move comfortable
to hold it this way

25:57.264 --> 25:59.183
than it is this way.

25:59.183 --> 26:01.268
Everything else
held together tightly,

26:01.268 --> 26:05.064
but there's no denying that's
a pretty significant roll.

26:05.064 --> 26:06.482
Frank, you're up.
Are you ready?

26:06.482 --> 26:07.775
- Let's do it.

26:07.775 --> 26:10.944
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:10.944 --> 26:12.988
<i>I know I heat-treated</i>
<i>that edge correctly</i>

26:12.988 --> 26:15.074
<i>and the blade is strong.</i>

26:15.074 --> 26:17.785
I'm just hoping, that warp,
nothing will happen there.

26:17.785 --> 26:19.369
That's my main concern.

26:19.369 --> 26:26.293
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:31.548 --> 26:35.761
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

26:35.761 --> 26:39.139
- So, Frank, you can see
it took a little bend,

26:39.139 --> 26:42.601
but the good news is that
your edge held up really well.

26:42.601 --> 26:44.770
Your handle
was very comfortable.

26:44.770 --> 26:46.688
The shape of it
was easy to control.

26:46.688 --> 26:48.899
I could index very easily,

26:48.899 --> 26:51.944
but there's no denying it took
a pretty significant bend.

26:51.944 --> 26:53.821
<i>- I see that bend in my blade</i>

26:53.821 --> 26:55.447
and it got me nervous,
you know?

26:55.447 --> 26:56.782
All of our blades
suffered damage,

26:56.782 --> 26:58.492
<i>so it's up in the air now.</i>

26:58.492 --> 27:00.536
<i>Anything can happen.</i>

27:00.536 --> 27:03.288
- All right, gentlemen.
This is the sharpness test.

27:03.288 --> 27:05.499
I'll be slicing
through these apples.

27:05.499 --> 27:07.751
What I'm looking for
is a really clean cut

27:07.751 --> 27:10.254
where we're splitting apples
as opposed to breaking them

27:10.254 --> 27:11.964
or just pushing them
out of the way.

27:11.964 --> 27:14.133
And, unlike the strength test,

27:14.133 --> 27:17.177
this test is all about what
your knives do to the apples.

27:17.177 --> 27:18.637
Tony, you're up.
Are you ready?

27:18.637 --> 27:20.013
- Yes, I am.
- Okay.

27:20.013 --> 27:26.937
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:28.021 --> 27:35.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:36.238 --> 27:38.740
All right, so your edge
is very sharp,

27:38.740 --> 27:41.451
even on the damage here
where it deflected.

27:41.451 --> 27:43.829
I mean, you can see the apples,
it went right through them,

27:43.829 --> 27:46.665
and even with that notch,
cut beautifully.

27:46.665 --> 27:48.458
Well done.
Really well done.

27:48.458 --> 27:49.877
- Thank you. Thank you.
- All right, Corey.

27:49.877 --> 27:51.587
You're up.
Are you ready?

27:51.587 --> 27:54.631
- We'll see what it can do.
- All right.

27:54.631 --> 27:56.842
<i>- I'm definitely</i>
<i>a little nervous right now.</i>

27:56.842 --> 27:59.678
With all my catastrophic
edge deflection,

27:59.678 --> 28:01.555
<i>I feel like you'd have</i>
<i>a better chance</i>

28:01.555 --> 28:04.182
<i>chopping through apples</i>
<i>with a ping pong paddle.</i>

28:04.182 --> 28:07.386
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:10.814 --> 28:13.650
<i>- With all my catastrophic</i>
<i>edge deflection,</i>

28:13.650 --> 28:16.987
there's just no chance
it's gonna be able to perform.

28:16.987 --> 28:21.033
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:23.869 --> 28:26.163
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:26.163 --> 28:29.374
- All right, so the apple kind
of tells the tale right there.

28:29.374 --> 28:33.253
You can see,
that dip in the apple?

28:33.253 --> 28:36.256
What happened is
it just skated the blade

28:36.256 --> 28:38.133
up and out of the way.

28:38.133 --> 28:41.219
With so much edge damage,
it's just not a cutter.

28:41.219 --> 28:42.804
Frank, you're up.
Are you ready?

28:42.804 --> 28:44.598
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

28:44.598 --> 28:51.563
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:52.606 --> 28:59.863
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:59.863 --> 29:05.035
So, Frank, your blade is plenty
sharp and actually cuts fine.

29:05.035 --> 29:06.995
The problem is that warp.

29:06.995 --> 29:09.456
With the warp in that blade,
as it moves across,

29:09.456 --> 29:11.208
it just starts pulling up,

29:11.208 --> 29:13.085
and once it starts
changing direction,

29:13.085 --> 29:15.420
it just flies up
out of those apples.

29:15.420 --> 29:19.675
I mean, you can actually see
this big curve up in the cuts,

29:19.675 --> 29:21.218
but it's sharp.

29:21.218 --> 29:23.011
It's still a cutter.
Nicely done.

29:23.011 --> 29:25.514
- Thank you.

29:25.514 --> 29:28.475
- Bladesmiths, the judges have
made their final decision.

29:28.475 --> 29:31.019
The bladesmith
leaving the Forge is...

29:31.019 --> 29:34.523
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:34.523 --> 29:37.985
Corey. Your blade
did not make the cut.

29:37.985 --> 29:40.904
- Well, Corey, although
Frank's blade did take a bend,

29:40.904 --> 29:42.906
yours took, unfortunately,

29:42.906 --> 29:45.617
<i>a catastrophic and</i>
<i>irreparable edge failure,</i>

29:45.617 --> 29:48.328
and it's for that reason
we had to let you go.

29:48.328 --> 29:52.207
- Corey, I have to ask you to
please surrender your weapon.

29:52.207 --> 29:54.584
<i>- Typically, you don't forge</i>
<i>out of gun barrels,</i>

29:54.584 --> 29:56.837
but steel is steel.

29:56.837 --> 29:58.755
<i>A knife is a knife.</i>

29:58.755 --> 30:00.966
We were all set on
an even playing field,

30:00.966 --> 30:04.011
and I was outperformed.

30:04.011 --> 30:05.846
<i>From here, go back home,</i>

30:05.846 --> 30:07.764
get right back into
swinging a hammer.

30:07.764 --> 30:11.393
<i>Just keep getting</i>
<i>better at it.</i>

30:11.393 --> 30:14.021
- Frank, Tony,
congratulations.

30:14.021 --> 30:16.314
You've made it to the final
round of this competition,

30:16.314 --> 30:18.859
which means that you're both
one step closer to the title

30:18.859 --> 30:21.194
and ten grand.

30:21.194 --> 30:23.071
Now we're sending you back
to your home forges

30:23.071 --> 30:25.323
to re-create an iconic
weapon from history...

30:25.323 --> 30:27.826
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:27.826 --> 30:31.496
the Sica Sword.

30:31.496 --> 30:33.707
<i>The Sica is a short</i>
<i>but dangerous sword</i>

30:33.707 --> 30:36.126
<i>widely used by gladiators</i>
<i>in ancient Rome.</i>

30:36.126 --> 30:38.253
<i>Since it was customary</i>
<i>to fight with armor,</i>

30:38.253 --> 30:40.672
<i>the blade featured a sharp</i>
<i>curve specifically designed</i>

30:40.672 --> 30:42.466
<i>to get around</i>
<i>an opponent's shield.</i>

30:42.466 --> 30:44.426
<i>A gruesome killer,</i>
<i>warriors would use</i>

30:44.426 --> 30:46.636
<i>its lethal inner edge</i>
<i>to sever limbs,</i>

30:46.636 --> 30:48.388
<i>or the blade's lethal point</i>
<i>to hook into the jaw</i>

30:48.388 --> 30:50.474
<i>and pierce through the head.</i>

30:50.474 --> 30:52.601
<i>Today, the Sica's often</i>
<i>depicted in popular culture</i>

30:52.601 --> 30:54.478
<i>during graphic</i>
<i>gladiator battles,</i>

30:54.478 --> 30:56.396
<i>most notably in</i>
<i>the television series</i>

30:56.396 --> 31:00.275
<i>"Spartacus: Blood and Sand."</i>

31:00.275 --> 31:04.696
The blade itself must include
an angled, double edged blade.

31:04.696 --> 31:08.450
Your blade must also
include a guard and pommel.

31:08.450 --> 31:11.244
<i>- It's basically a bent sword.</i>

31:11.244 --> 31:15.290
I've never built a bent sword,
at least not on purpose.

31:15.290 --> 31:17.042
<i>[chuckles]</i>

31:17.042 --> 31:18.418
- You will have five days
at your home forge

31:18.418 --> 31:20.587
to complete this project.

31:20.587 --> 31:22.255
At the end of those five days,
you will return to present

31:22.255 --> 31:24.716
your Sica swords
to our panel of expert judges.

31:24.716 --> 31:27.552
Good luck, bladesmiths.
We'll see you in five days.

31:27.552 --> 31:32.307
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:32.307 --> 31:34.684
<i>- Welcome to my forge</i>
<i>in Scotts Mills, Oregon.</i>

31:34.684 --> 31:38.772
We're building a [indistinct]
gladiator sword.

31:38.772 --> 31:41.149
It's gonna be three steel,
Damascus, 15 and 20,

31:41.149 --> 31:44.027
1084 and 1095.

31:44.027 --> 31:47.572
Pretty simple, right?
[laughs]

31:47.572 --> 31:49.908
<i>The biggest thing I got to do</i>
<i>is get my welds perfect,</i>

31:49.908 --> 31:52.494
<i>because if they aren't tight,</i>

31:52.494 --> 31:54.704
<i>my billet can fall</i>
<i>into pieces.</i>

31:54.704 --> 31:57.124
<i>Bending a piece of steel</i>
<i>can be difficult.</i>

31:57.124 --> 32:00.544
It's a drastic bend,
but I got this.

32:00.544 --> 32:03.088
Leave it to the Romans, right?

32:03.088 --> 32:06.341
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:06.341 --> 32:09.845
- Here we go.
Whoo!

32:09.845 --> 32:11.805
<i>The hardest part</i>
<i>about forging this blade</i>

32:11.805 --> 32:14.516
is trying to nail that angle.

32:14.516 --> 32:19.104
I've made curved blades
before, nothing like this.

32:19.104 --> 32:21.606
We're getting there.
I just got to keep going.

32:21.606 --> 32:23.400
<i>Being a plumber at a zoo,</i>

32:23.400 --> 32:26.153
<i>I'm around a lot</i>
<i>of intense situations.</i>

32:26.153 --> 32:28.572
<i>Try doing plumbing</i>
<i>for an elephant,</i>

32:28.572 --> 32:31.366
and see if you can
get through that.

32:31.366 --> 32:34.369
Bada bing, bada boom,
and that's at 27.

32:34.369 --> 32:36.454
Wow, that looks like
a hockey stick.

32:36.454 --> 32:38.748
Try to profile out
that tip a little bit.

32:38.748 --> 32:40.792
<i>I definitely have to be</i>
<i>the underdog here.</i>

32:40.792 --> 32:42.794
<i>How could I not be?</i>

32:42.794 --> 32:45.630
Tony's got experience almost
as long as I've been born,

32:45.630 --> 32:47.924
<i>but I'm confident in my work.</i>

32:47.924 --> 32:50.427
Good job.

32:50.427 --> 32:52.971
<i>- Today is the heat treat.</i>

32:52.971 --> 32:56.016
The heat treat is what
gives the blade life.

32:56.016 --> 32:59.144
Without a good heat treat,
you just have a hunk of steel.

32:59.144 --> 33:04.399
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:04.399 --> 33:08.737
Oh, wow.
It's got a bow in it.

33:08.737 --> 33:11.072
I have to get
this warp out fast.

33:11.072 --> 33:13.700
<i>If I don't, I'm screwed.</i>

33:13.700 --> 33:15.869
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:15.869 --> 33:18.163
<i>- Yesterday, I was able</i>
<i>to accomplish</i>

33:18.163 --> 33:20.248
<i>the profile of that blade.</i>

33:20.248 --> 33:22.876
<i>Today, I plan on getting</i>
<i>the blade heat treated.</i>

33:22.876 --> 33:25.795
The quench tank I have now
is a little too thin,

33:25.795 --> 33:27.631
<i>and the blade will not fit,</i>

33:27.631 --> 33:30.675
<i>so I had to come up</i>
<i>with something.</i>

33:30.675 --> 33:32.802
You really shouldn't make a
quench tank out of a wood box.

33:32.802 --> 33:34.429
<i>There's usually</i>
<i>a lot of flames</i>

33:34.429 --> 33:36.139
<i>when you quench a blade,</i>

33:36.139 --> 33:37.891
<i>so it could definitely</i>
<i>flame up.</i>

33:37.891 --> 33:39.768
This is always the most
nerve-racking part.

33:39.768 --> 33:42.729
If there's a crack,
then I'm screwed.

33:42.729 --> 33:44.648
The longer the blade is,

33:44.648 --> 33:46.900
the more likely it is
to cause a problem.

33:46.900 --> 33:52.239
<i>During the quench, it could</i>
<i>warp or break or shatter.</i>

33:52.239 --> 33:54.491
<i>If the quench doesn't</i>
<i>go right today,</i>

33:54.491 --> 33:56.634
<i>all that work could</i>
<i>just be for nothing.</i>

33:59.120 --> 34:00.914
<i>- I really put</i>
<i>everything I had</i>

34:00.914 --> 34:03.917
<i>into getting</i>
<i>this angle right,</i>

34:03.917 --> 34:06.336
and during the quench,
the blade could warp,

34:06.336 --> 34:09.422
<i>or break or shatter.</i>

34:09.422 --> 34:12.092
<i>All that work could</i>
<i>just be for nothing.</i>

34:12.092 --> 34:18.056
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:18.056 --> 34:20.475
No warps!

34:20.475 --> 34:22.477
Overall,
my blade looks awesome.

34:22.477 --> 34:24.813
<i>I can't wait to see</i>
<i>the finished product.</i>

34:24.813 --> 34:26.314
<i>I'm excited.</i>

34:26.314 --> 34:28.233
We did it, boys!

34:28.233 --> 34:30.652
<i>- I was able to fix the warp,</i>

34:30.652 --> 34:34.072
<i>so today I'm putting it</i>
<i>in the acid to etch it.</i>

34:34.072 --> 34:37.075
<i>I think we're gonna have</i>
<i>a really super cool design.</i>

34:37.075 --> 34:39.035
<i>Frank does great work.</i>

34:39.035 --> 34:41.162
<i>I believe</i>
<i>I do great work also.</i>

34:41.162 --> 34:45.041
<i>It's gonna come down</i>
<i>to the finish details.</i>

34:45.041 --> 34:48.586
For the handle,
I use the mahogany wenge.

34:48.586 --> 34:50.088
<i>Mahogany's</i>
<i>a lighter material.</i>

34:50.088 --> 34:51.631
<i>Wenge's a really</i>
<i>dark material,</i>

34:51.631 --> 34:53.800
so they make
a good contrast.

34:53.800 --> 34:55.969
<i>And then I used brass</i>
<i>as part of the blade guard,</i>

34:55.969 --> 34:58.054
<i>and put the</i>
<i>pieces together.</i>

34:58.054 --> 35:00.599
<i>I believe this sword</i>
<i>will outperform Frank's,</i>

35:00.599 --> 35:02.851
<i>both aesthetically</i>
<i>and functionally.</i>

35:02.851 --> 35:05.186
I think it will work.

35:05.186 --> 35:08.064
<i>- Even though I feel a</i>
<i>big load is off my shoulders,</i>

35:08.064 --> 35:09.524
<i>this is no time to relax</i>

35:09.524 --> 35:11.735
because anything
could go wrong.

35:11.735 --> 35:14.779
<i>I'm doing a seven-piece</i>
<i>construction with nine pins</i>

35:14.779 --> 35:16.906
<i>holding it all in place.</i>

35:16.906 --> 35:19.159
<i>This is the first time</i>
<i>I've ever done a hidden tang</i>

35:19.159 --> 35:20.452
<i>through a set of scales.</i>

35:20.452 --> 35:22.120
<i>All this stuff is gonna show</i>

35:22.120 --> 35:24.539
<i>and put me apart</i>
<i>from Tony's blade.</i>

35:24.539 --> 35:26.791
<i>All I got to do is shape it,</i>

35:26.791 --> 35:29.878
<i>and polish it, and sharpen it,</i>
<i>and it's ready to go.</i>

35:29.878 --> 35:32.297
Oh, look at this.

35:32.297 --> 35:35.300
A message from my competitor.

35:35.300 --> 35:37.385
"Looking forward to the test."

35:37.385 --> 35:38.803
Ha ha ha.

35:38.803 --> 35:40.430
"I can't wait."

35:40.430 --> 35:42.182
Time to do some battle.

35:42.182 --> 35:44.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:44.267 --> 35:46.936
- Frank, Tony, welcome
back to the Forge.

35:46.936 --> 35:48.438
You've had five days
at your home forges

35:48.438 --> 35:50.190
to work on your Sica Swords.

35:50.190 --> 35:52.025
Frank, tell us
about your blade.

35:52.025 --> 35:54.736
<i>- I did 1095 high carbon steel</i>

35:54.736 --> 35:56.946
<i>with African Blackwood guard,</i>

35:56.946 --> 35:59.074
<i>with a Texas pecan handle.</i>

35:59.074 --> 36:00.950
It's the best blade
I ever made.

36:00.950 --> 36:04.079
- Great.
Tony, tell us about your blade.

36:04.079 --> 36:06.831
<i>- I used 1095, 1084,</i>

36:06.831 --> 36:09.000
<i>and 15 and 20</i>
<i>for the cutting edges,</i>

36:09.000 --> 36:10.794
<i>and I have cable</i>
<i>going down the center</i>

36:10.794 --> 36:13.088
<i>as the serpent</i>
<i>in the sword.</i>

36:13.088 --> 36:16.132
- Well, gentlemen, both of
your blades look fantastic,

36:16.132 --> 36:19.010
but are they strong,
deadly, and sharp?

36:19.010 --> 36:22.013
Doug.

36:22.013 --> 36:24.849
- Bladesmiths,
this is the kill test.

36:24.849 --> 36:26.685
We'll take you Sica Sword

36:26.685 --> 36:29.145
and deliver killing blows
on this ballistics dummy.

36:29.145 --> 36:30.980
Frank, you're up first.
Are you ready?

36:30.980 --> 36:33.566
- Hell, yeah.
- Let's do this.

36:33.566 --> 36:35.694
- I'm feeling good,
yet anxious.

36:35.694 --> 36:37.862
<i>I put my all</i>
<i>into this blade.</i>

36:37.862 --> 36:39.280
I'm just hoping
it just takes the head

36:39.280 --> 36:41.199
right off of this dummy.

36:41.199 --> 36:43.785
- Bladesmiths, I'm still
recuperating from an injury,

36:43.785 --> 36:45.870
so please welcome
Staff Sergeant

36:45.870 --> 36:47.580
Chris Mans
of the U. S. Army.

36:47.580 --> 36:49.290
Today, he will
have the pleasure

36:49.290 --> 36:51.543
of testing your weapon.

36:51.543 --> 36:58.508
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:06.015 --> 37:09.853
- Nice.
- [exhales]

37:09.853 --> 37:11.479
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:11.479 --> 37:14.858
- Well, Frank,
your blade is sharp.

37:14.858 --> 37:17.610
In combat, the Sica is
sometimes used in its curve

37:17.610 --> 37:19.654
to pull away the sword
and come in.

37:19.654 --> 37:22.407
In this case,
it pulled away the head.

37:22.407 --> 37:25.952
Overall,
your weapon will kill.

37:25.952 --> 37:27.620
- Thank you.
- Tony, you ready?

37:27.620 --> 37:31.040
- Mm-hmm.
- Let's have some fun.

37:31.040 --> 37:33.334
- Frank's blade
just did awesome in this.

37:33.334 --> 37:35.420
<i>I mean, the head came off.</i>

37:35.420 --> 37:37.922
<i>I'm hoping mine</i>
<i>will do the same thing,</i>

37:37.922 --> 37:40.967
and just unleash hell
onto this dummy.

37:40.967 --> 37:48.141
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:48.975 --> 37:52.228
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:52.228 --> 37:55.732
[laughs]

37:55.732 --> 37:59.527
- All right, Tony, this is
a scary Sica sword.

37:59.527 --> 38:01.988
On the initial hack
into the chest cavity,

38:01.988 --> 38:04.157
it penetrated so deep,

38:04.157 --> 38:07.410
it totally demolished
this ballistics dummy.

38:07.410 --> 38:10.497
Overall, sir,
your weapon will kill.

38:10.497 --> 38:13.708
- Tony's blade just performs
great on this thing.

38:13.708 --> 38:15.710
<i>I mean, even though</i>
<i>they both will kill,</i>

38:15.710 --> 38:17.879
<i>his just looked a little bit</i>
<i>more violent,</i>

38:17.879 --> 38:20.548
so it has me a little--
a little nervous.

38:20.548 --> 38:22.675
- Gentlemen,
this is the strength test.

38:22.675 --> 38:25.178
In order to test the strength
and durability of your blades,

38:25.178 --> 38:27.055
I'm gonna attack these shields.

38:27.055 --> 38:28.640
Remember,
this test is all about

38:28.640 --> 38:30.308
what the shields
do to your weapons

38:30.308 --> 38:32.060
and not what your weapons
do to the shields.

38:32.060 --> 38:33.311
Frank, you're up first.
Are you ready?

38:33.311 --> 38:35.814
- Yep, let's do this.

38:35.814 --> 38:37.732
My stomach's in knots
right now.

38:37.732 --> 38:39.400
<i>I'm just hoping</i>
<i>the tip of my blade</i>

38:39.400 --> 38:41.402
<i>doesn't break off</i>
<i>on that shield.</i>

38:41.402 --> 38:43.780
<i>Tony's blade is awesome,</i>

38:43.780 --> 38:46.115
<i>so my blade</i>
<i>has to perform perfectly.</i>

38:46.115 --> 38:47.450
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:50.286 --> 38:52.497
- I'm just hoping
the tip of my blade

38:52.497 --> 38:55.458
doesn't break off
on that shield.

38:55.458 --> 39:02.382
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:03.424 --> 39:08.721
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:08.721 --> 39:11.182
Whew.
- [chuckles]

39:11.182 --> 39:14.060
- Well, Frank, your edge
held up perfectly.

39:14.060 --> 39:16.145
- All right.
- It's still straight.

39:16.145 --> 39:18.189
It's still sharp.

39:18.189 --> 39:20.316
Everything is still
tight and solid.

39:20.316 --> 39:22.193
Well done.
- Thank you.

39:22.193 --> 39:24.028
- Tony, you're up next.
Are you ready?

39:24.028 --> 39:26.739
- Yes. I'm totally nervous
about the shield.

39:26.739 --> 39:28.533
It's got to hold its edge.

39:28.533 --> 39:31.327
This thing's purpose
built for gladiators.

39:31.327 --> 39:33.204
It has to perform.

39:33.204 --> 39:39.919
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:41.170 --> 39:48.136
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:49.512 --> 39:51.890
- Well, Tony, your edge

39:51.890 --> 39:54.309
held up perfectly as well,
razor sharp.

39:54.309 --> 39:58.062
I see no problem with
the edge from the shield.

39:58.062 --> 40:00.857
In all, a nice solid blade.
Well done.

40:00.857 --> 40:03.735
- Thank you.
- Good job, man.

40:03.735 --> 40:06.446
- All right, gentlemen,
now it's the sharpness test.

40:06.446 --> 40:08.406
I'll be cutting through
this sugar cane.

40:08.406 --> 40:10.158
One cut with the front edge
of your blade,

40:10.158 --> 40:11.868
one cut with the back edge.

40:11.868 --> 40:13.161
All right, Frank, you're
up first. Are you ready?

40:13.161 --> 40:16.497
- Hell, yes.

40:16.497 --> 40:23.421
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:26.591 --> 40:28.551
- All right,
Frank, right off,

40:28.551 --> 40:31.054
your blade's got
a really nice balance to it.

40:31.054 --> 40:34.140
You can see, on that first cut,
it kind of pulled in my hand,

40:34.140 --> 40:36.351
but it's still a good feel.

40:36.351 --> 40:38.686
On the back cut,
it blew right through.

40:38.686 --> 40:41.230
Any gladiator using this would
be quick, would be deadly.

40:41.230 --> 40:43.274
Well done.
- Thank you.

40:43.274 --> 40:44.567
- All right, Tony, you're up.
Are you ready for this?

40:44.567 --> 40:46.736
- Yep.

40:46.736 --> 40:48.404
<i>I'm a little nervous</i>
<i>because this is going to be</i>

40:48.404 --> 40:50.448
to test of the performance
of my blade.

40:50.448 --> 40:52.909
Without a great cutting edge,
you don't have a blade.

40:52.909 --> 40:56.245
<i>It's time for my blade</i>
<i>to pony up.</i>

40:56.245 --> 41:03.169
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:06.464 --> 41:09.050
- So, Tony, is it sharp?
Yes.

41:09.050 --> 41:11.427
It's very sharp,
and it cut very nicely.

41:11.427 --> 41:13.763
Still right.
Still tight. Well done.

41:13.763 --> 41:15.139
- Thank you.

41:15.139 --> 41:17.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:17.266 --> 41:19.811
- Bladesmiths, over
the course of three rounds,

41:19.811 --> 41:21.229
both of you has displayed

41:21.229 --> 41:23.564
excellent
bladesmithing talents.

41:23.564 --> 41:25.525
However, in this arena
of competition,

41:25.525 --> 41:27.318
there can only be
one champion.

41:27.318 --> 41:30.363
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:30.363 --> 41:32.532
Tony, congratulations.

41:32.532 --> 41:35.410
You are the new
"Forged in Fire" champion.

41:35.410 --> 41:38.579
Frank, unfortunately, your
weapon did not make the cut.

41:38.579 --> 41:40.540
- Frank, first off,
I want to say

41:40.540 --> 41:43.126
that there are no losers
in this round,

41:43.126 --> 41:45.044
but we can only
pick one winner.

41:45.044 --> 41:46.879
Both weapons were very sharp.

41:46.879 --> 41:48.673
Both weapons were very strong,

41:48.673 --> 41:51.551
but the Sica was
a gladiator's weapon,

41:51.551 --> 41:54.178
and your weapon was
outperformed in the kill test.

41:54.178 --> 41:56.097
It's for that reason
we're sending you home.

41:56.097 --> 41:58.641
- I totally understand.

41:58.641 --> 42:01.728
- Frank, please
surrender your blade.

42:01.728 --> 42:03.479
<i>- I'm fine with this result.</i>

42:03.479 --> 42:08.276
They both killed,
but his really killed.

42:08.276 --> 42:11.154
<i>Tony's already invited me</i>
<i>to come up there and forge.</i>

42:11.154 --> 42:13.031
<i>He's gonna</i>
<i>show me some stuff.</i>

42:13.031 --> 42:17.285
I'll know Tony probably
the rest of my life.

42:17.285 --> 42:19.120
- Tony, congratulations.

42:19.120 --> 42:21.289
You are our new
"Forged in Fire" champion.

42:21.289 --> 42:23.833
and that's a title that comes
with a check for ten grand.

42:23.833 --> 42:25.710
Good job.
How do you feel right now?

42:25.710 --> 42:28.337
- I feel pretty good.
- All right, well, Tony,

42:28.337 --> 42:31.174
please present your weapon
to the judges.

42:31.174 --> 42:33.551
- Just a pinch.
Okay, I'm still here.

42:33.551 --> 42:35.136
It's not a dream.

42:35.136 --> 42:37.638
<i>I won.</i>
<i>It's awesome.</i>

42:37.638 --> 42:41.434
How do you put it in words?
I came, I saw, and I conquered.

42:41.434 --> 42:47.440
<i>♪ ♪</i>
